text: Plum Creek is a stream in Kossuth and Hancock counties, in the U.S. state of Hancock County, Iowa. It is a tributary of the east fork of the Des Moines River. Plum Creek was named for the wild plum trees lining its banks. ==See also== *List of rivers of Iowa ==References== Category:Bodies of water of Hancock County, Iowa Category:Bodies of water of Kossuth County, Iowa Category:Rivers of Iowa
